SIMPLE: weatherboard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weatherboard
<hw>Weath"er*board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>That side of a vessel which is
toward the wind; the windward side.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A piece of
plank placed in a porthole, or other opening, to keep out
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A board extending
from the ridge to the eaves along the slope of the gable, and forming a
close junction between the shingling of a roof and the side of the
building beneath.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A clapboard or feather-edged
board used in weatherboarding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weather-board</ent>⟦br⟧
